TY  - JOUR
T1  - Management Theory and Social Welfare: Contributions and Challenges
AU  - Jones, Thomas M.
AU  - Donaldson, Thomas
AU  - Freeman, R. Edward
AU  - Harrison, Jeffrey S.
AU  - Leana, Carrie R.
AU  - Mahoney, Joseph T.
AU  - Pearce, Jone L.
Y1  - 2016/01/12
PY  - 2016
DA  - 2016/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2016.0012
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2016.0012
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 216
EP  - 228
VL  - 41
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this Introduction to the Special Topic Forum on Management Theory and Social Welfare, we first provide an overview of the motivation behind the special issue. We then highlight the contributions of the six articles that make up this forum and identify some common themes. We also suggest some reasons why social welfare issues are so difficult to address in the context of management theory. In addition, we evaluate means of assessing social welfare and urge scholars not to make (or imply) unwarranted ?wealth creation? claims.
